🛒 Shopping App – Workflow Diagram Description

The workflow diagram represents how users interact with different parts of the shopping application and how the application processes user actions.

The application begins from the main() function, which launches the main application widget and loads the Home Screen.


---

1️⃣ Application Start

The execution of the application begins with the main() function.

The runApp() method launches the main application widget.

The app loads the Home Screen, which displays products, search functionality, and category filters.


Process Flow:

Start
 ↓
main()
 ↓
runApp(ShoppingApp)
 ↓
Home Screen Loaded


---

2️⃣ Home Screen Interaction

The Home Screen acts as the central hub of the application.

It contains:

Greeting message

Search bar

Category filters (All, Fashion, Tech, Home, Sports, Beauty)

Flash sale banner

Product grid displaying multiple products


Users can perform several actions from this screen.

Possible actions:

Search products

Filter products by category

View product details

Add products to cart

Add products to wishlist


Process Flow:

Home Screen
   ↓
User Selects Action
   ↓
Search / Filter / Product Click / Add to Cart / Wishlist


---

3️⃣ Product Detail Screen

When a user taps on a product card, the application navigates to the Product Detail Screen.

This screen displays:

Product image

Product description

Price

Star rating

Size selection options

Add to Cart button

Add to Wishlist button


From this screen, users can add the product to their cart or wishlist.

Process Flow:

Product Selected
     ↓
Open Product Detail Screen
     ↓
View Product Information
     ↓
Add to Cart OR Add to Wishlist


---

4️⃣ Cart Management

The Cart Screen allows users to manage selected items.

Features include:

Viewing items added to cart

Increasing quantity (+)

Decreasing quantity (−)

Removing items

Viewing subtotal and total price

Checkout option


Process Flow:

Cart Screen
   ↓
View Cart Items
   ↓
Modify Quantity OR Remove Item
   ↓
View Total Price
   ↓
Checkout


---

5️⃣ Wishlist Management

The Wishlist Screen stores products that users want to purchase later.

Users can:

View saved products

Remove items from wishlist

Move items to cart


Process Flow:

Wishlist Screen
    ↓
View Saved Products
    ↓
Add to Cart OR Remove


---

6️⃣ Checkout Process

When the user presses the Checkout button, the system processes the order.

Actions performed:

Order confirmation

Cart cleared

Order count increased in user profile


Process Flow:

Checkout Button
      ↓
Order Processed
      ↓
Cart Cleared
      ↓
Order Count Updated


---

7️⃣ Profile Screen

The Profile Screen displays user information and application settings.

It includes:

Total orders

Wishlist item count

Saved addresses

Payment methods

Application settings

Logout option


Process Flow:

Profile Screen
     ↓
View Account Information
     ↓
Manage Settings / Logout


---

📊 Complete Application Workflow (Summary)

Start
 ↓
Launch App
 ↓
Home Screen
 ↓
Search / Filter / Select Product
 ↓
Product Detail Screen
 ↓
Add to Cart OR Add to Wishlist
 ↓
Cart Screen
 ↓
Modify Items
 ↓
Checkout
 ↓
Order Completed


